modules.description: This module offers creation, in-place manipulation, and transformation operations for polymorphic arrays, supporting indexed access, bulk updates, and functional iterations. It specializes in handling C-style arrays (`'a Carray.t`) while enabling seamless conversion to and from OCaml's standard arrays, with non-allocating slicing for efficient sub-array views. Typical applications include performance-sensitive numerical processing, interfacing with C libraries requiring contiguous memory layouts, and zero-copy data sharing between OCaml and C-compatible array representations.
